name: EA-004-Hypatia
description:
Hypatia (360 - 415 aC) was a Greek Neoplatonic philosopher of Roman Egypt. She was the first woman documented to have been a mathematician. As head of the Platonic school in Alexandria, he also taught philosophy and astronomy

Digital Watercolor Vector Illustration made in Adobe Photoshop, 1200x1200px, 200dpi, JPEG
